  "solution": [
    "## Solutions to Determinant Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: 2×2 Matrix Determinants",
    "",
    "**a)** $$ \\begin{vmatrix} 3 & 4 \\\\ 1 & 2 \\end{vmatrix} = 3 \\times 2 - 4 \\times 1 = 6 - 4 = 2 $$",
    "",
    "**b)** $$ \\begin{vmatrix} -2 & 5 \\\\ 7 & -1 \\end{vmatrix} = (-2) \\times (-1) - 5 \\times 7 = 2 - 35 = -33 $$",
    "",
    "**c)** $$ \\begin{vmatrix} 0 & 6 \\\\ 8 & 0 \\end{vmatrix} = 0 \\times 0 - 6 \\times 8 = 0 - 48 = -48 $$",
    "",
    "**d)** $$ \\begin{vmatrix} a & b \\\\ c & d \\end{vmatrix} = ad - bc $$",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: 3×3 Matrix Determinants",
    "",
    "**a)** $$ \\begin{vmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 \\\\ 4 & 5 & 6 \\\\ 7 & 8 & 9 \\end{vmatrix} = 1(5\\times9-6\\times8) - 2(4\\times9-6\\times7) + 3(4\\times8-5\\times7) $$",
    "$$ = 1(45-48) - 2(36-42) + 3(32-35) = 1(-3) - 2(-6) + 3(-3) = -3 + 12 - 9 = 0 $$",
    "",
    "**b)** $$ \\begin{vmatrix} 2 & -1 & 3 \\\\ 1 & 0 & 4 \\\\ -2 & 1 & 5 \\end{vmatrix} = 2(0\\times5-4\\times1) - (-1)(1\\times5-4\\times(-2)) + 3(1\\times1-0\\times(-2)) $$",
    "$$ = 2(0-4) - (-1)(5+8) + 3(1-0) = 2(-4) - (-1)(13) + 3(1) = -8 + 13 + 3 = 8 $$",
    "",
    "**c)** $$ \\begin{vmatrix} 1 & 0 & 0 \\\\ 0 & 2 & 0 \\\\ 0 & 0 & 3 \\end{vmatrix} = 1 \\times 2 \\times 3 = 6 $$",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Laplace Expansion Along First Row",
    "",
    "**a)** Matrix: $$ \\begin{pmatrix} 2 & 3 & 1 \\\\ 1 & 2 & 3 \\\\ 3 & 1 & 2 \\end{pmatrix} $$",
    "det = 2×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 2 & 3 \\\\ 1 & 2 \\end{vmatrix}$$ - 3×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 1 & 3 \\\\ 3 & 2 \\end{vmatrix}$$ + 1×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 1 & 2 \\\\ 3 & 1 \\end{vmatrix}$$",
    "= 2(4-3) - 3(2-9) + 1(2-6) = 2(1) - 3(-7) + 1(-4) = 2 + 21 - 4 = 19",
    "",
    "**b)** Matrix: $$ \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 & 2 \\\\ 3 & 1 & 1 \\\\ 2 & 2 & 0 \\end{pmatrix} $$",
    "det = 1×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 1 & 1 \\\\ 2 & 0 \\end{vmatrix}$$ - 0×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 3 & 1 \\\\ 2 & 0 \\end{vmatrix}$$ + 2×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 3 & 1 \\\\ 2 & 2 \\end{vmatrix}$$",
    "= 1(0-2) - 0 + 2(6-2) = 1(-2) + 2(4) = -2 + 8 = 6",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Laplace Expansion Along First Column",
    "",
    "**a)** Matrix: $$ \\begin{pmatrix} 4 & 1 & 2 \\\\ 2 & 3 & 1 \\\\ 1 & 2 & 3 \\end{pmatrix} $$",
    "det = 4×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 3 & 1 \\\\ 2 & 3 \\end{vmatrix}$$ - 2×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 1 & 2 \\\\ 2 & 3 \\end{vmatrix}$$ + 1×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 1 & 2 \\\\ 3 & 1 \\end{vmatrix}$$",
    "= 4(9-2) - 2(3-4) + 1(3-6) = 4(7) - 2(-1) + 1(-3) = 28 + 2 - 3 = 27",
    "",
    "**b)** Matrix: $$ \\begin{pmatrix} 3 & 2 & 1 \\\\ 1 & 0 & 2 \\\\ 2 & 1 & 0 \\end{pmatrix} $$",
    "det = 3×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 0 & 2 \\\\ 1 & 0 \\end{vmatrix}$$ - 1×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 2 & 1 \\\\ 1 & 0 \\end{vmatrix}$$ + 2×$$\\begin{vmatrix} 2 & 1 \\\\ 0 & 2 \\end{vmatrix}$$",
    "= 3(0-2) - 1(0-1) + 2(4-0) = 3(-2) - 1(-1) + 2(4) = -6 + 1 + 8 = 3",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: General Laplace Expansion",
    "",
    "**a)** Laplace expansion along row i:",
    "$$ \\det(A) = \\sum_{j=1}^{n} a_{ij} C_{ij} $$",
    "where C_ij is the cofactor of element a_ij",
    "",
    "**b)** Laplace expansion along column j:",
    "$$ \\det(A) = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} a_{ij} C_{ij} $$",
    "where C_ij is the cofactor of element a_ij",
    "",
    "**Cofactor definition:** C_ij = (-1)^(i+j) × det(M_ij)",
    "where M_ij is the minor matrix obtained by removing row i and column j from A"
